<p>Maybe he could still be attempting pranks on Foundation staff, but keeps running into his physical limits. Mounting frustration leads to a continuing pseudo-cheerful demeanor, but increasingly mean and dangerous prank attempts. Perhaps showing him gradually learning to cope with his disability and/or recovering faster than physical therapists were led to believe. Near the end, there could be breaches and staff deaths that they can't <em>prove</em> 746 is responsible for, but next day he's in the first legit good mood they've seen in a while.</p>
<p>As is, -1 for not hooking me.</p>

